Two suspects died and one was seriously injured in an attempted cash-in-transit robbery on Saturday morning in Limpopo.The SAPS made a major breakthrough on Saturday morning while in collaboration with several other units in Limpopo near Makopane they foiled a cash-in-transit robbery. Acting on tip-off from community members who had spotted a suspicious group of men on their way to rob a cash van, the community members called the police.The suspects were travelling in a Ford Ranger and the police attempted to stop the vehicle then the suspects opened fire. After a shoot-out two suspects were killed on the spot and one was seriously injured. The police arrested the other two suspects.The police discovered an R5-rifle and two 9mm pistols and on investigation discovered the vehicle they were travelling with was hijacked in Westernburg, just outside Polokwane. The police will continue with investigations and the two arrested men will appear at the Mokopane Magistrate Court on Monday .Meanwhile, the R24 near Barbara Road towards the airport in Ekurhuleni in Gauteng was blocked after a cash-in-transit robbery where suspects blew open armoured vehicle carrying the cash and made off with undisclosed amount of money.The Gauteng police are investigating and for help. Anybody with information should contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111.-TNA Reporter 